-- Japan PM Kan: wants BOJ to take appropriate policy steps: report
-- 
-- Thu May 19, 2011 8:56am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/05/19/us-japan-economy-kan-idUSTRE74I1G220110519

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Japanese Prime Minister Naoto Kan said on Thursday he expects the Bank of Japan to take appropriate and flexible monetary policy steps, Kyodo news agency reported. 

 Kan also told parliament's Lower House plenary session that the BOJ is prohibited by law from directly underwriting government bonds, Kyodo said. (Reporting by  Leika Kihara  and Rie Ishiguro; Editing by  Joseph Radford )